cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and dialog systems. The paper also uses computer vision techniques to encode sticker images, which suggests it could also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a deep learning model to learn the semantic meaning of stickers, which could fall under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The use of deep learning models also suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval and matching, which could place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category.
